  <subsection|Install software on your Shell >

  <\hde>
    \;

    <\enumerate>
      <item>Install Scoop (Windows) or Homebrew (macOS): <verbatim|https://scoop.sh/> or <verbatim|https://brew.sh/>

      <item><hlink|Install Claude Code with Scoop|https://dev.to/0xkoji/install-claude-code-on-windows-with-scoop-2452>

      <with|font-series|bold|Windows>

      <\shell>
        <\code>
          scoop install git

          setx CLAUDE_CODE_GIT_BASH_PATH "%USERPROFILE%\\scoop\\apps\\git\\current\\usr\\bin\\bash.exe"

          irm https://claude.ai/install.ps1 \| iex
        </code>
      </shell>

      <with|font-series|bold|macOS>

      <shell|brew install --cask claude-code>

      <item>Configure Claude Code with Kimi K2.5: <hlink|Kimi K2.5 on Claude Code|https://platform.moonshot.cn/docs/guide/agent-support#%E9%85%8D%E7%BD%AE%E7%8E%AF%E5%A2%83%E5%8F%98%E9%87%8F>. (You are also welcome to use other APIs)
    </enumerate>
